INSERT INTO program_sops (module_id, sop_number, title, content, quality_bars, deliverables, tools_used, dependencies, version)
VALUES (
  'm0',
  '0-3',
  'Write an ICP-Targeted LinkedIn Post',
  $body$## Why This Matters

The LinkedIn algorithm now shows content to people based on **relevance**, not just connection. A beginner with one follower can go viral if they write effectively and get engagement. The more narrowly you target your language to your ICP, the more the algorithm surfaces your content to the right people.

## The Formula That Works

Every high-performing ICP post follows a pattern:

1. **Call out your audience explicitly** — "If you're a [job title] at a [company type] struggling with [specific problem]..."
2. **Use the jargon of your industry** — Don't write generically. Use the exact words your ICP uses on a daily basis.
3. **Offer something specific and valuable** — A playbook, a blueprint, a walkthrough, a case study.
4. **Include a clear CTA** — "Comment [keyword] below" or "DM me [keyword]."

## Examples From the Cohort

**Felix (SaaS websites):** Created a blueprint on connecting Clay tables to Webflow for programmatic ABM landing pages. Called out "head of marketing of SaaS companies with a team of 50+ that are stuck with scaling their ABM campaigns." Result: 220+ comments, many from actual ICP.

**Alberto (industrial consulting):** Writes in Italian using heavy industry jargon for mechatronics and machinery companies. Posts regularly hit 5,000+ views with 30+ comments. He deliberately makes small "human" imperfections to differentiate from generic AI content.

**Stuart (operations consulting):** Targets specific gains: "Get 2.28x more output from your claims operation." Industry-specific, result-specific, audience-specific.

## Key Principles

**Write to one person.** In any individual post, you can only write to one person. Mentally imagine the exact person — their age, how long they've been in the job, the language they use, what their personal goals are, what worries them. Write to that person.

:::tip From the Field
To truly picture your ICP, run a 30-minute intake interview covering ~15 questions — including demographics (marital status, kids, geography) and behavioral traits — then pull a verified list of ~5,000 matching LinkedIn profiles. The litmus test: someone *outside* your ICP should read your post and feel nothing.
:::

**Use their jargon, not yours.** Ask AI to refine your posts using the specific terminology of your ICP's industry. The more specific and native the language feels, the better it performs.

**Narrow beats broad.** Counter-intuitively, the more you narrow your targeting, the more traction you get. LinkedIn rewards specificity because it can match your content to the right viewers.

:::tip From the Field
Write to a specific revenue stage, not a broad category. Instead of "tips to grow your SaaS," write "When you've just hit `$10M/yr`, here are the 3 problems you typically face…" — specificity of language IS the targeting mechanism on LinkedIn. Pair this with active ICP network growth (25-30 targeted connection requests/day); without a relevant connected audience, even great posts get limited distribution.
:::

**Don't sound like AI.** Make deliberate small imperfections. Add personal opinions. Reference specific situations. The goal isn't polish — it's authenticity and value.

## Post Frequency

3x per week minimum. You don't need to post every day. Consistency matters more than volume. Each post should target your ICP with specific, valuable content.

## The Organic → Ad Pipeline

Don't write "ads." Write organic posts. See which ones perform. Edit the winners to add an opt-in link. Boost those as Thought Leadership Ads (see [SOP 5.4](/sops/module-5-linkedin-ads/sop-5-4-select-boost-posts)). This removes all guesswork about what to advertise.$body$,
  '[{"check":"Post explicitly calls out target audience by job title, company type, or specific problem within first 1-2 sentences","severity":"critical"},{"check":"Language uses industry-specific jargon and terminology native to the ICP, not generic business language","severity":"critical"},{"check":"Post delivers one specific, valuable deliverable (playbook, blueprint, walkthrough, case study, metric, or insight)","severity":"critical"},{"check":"Clear call-to-action present (comment keyword, DM for resource, or engagement request)","severity":"critical"},{"check":"Post contains deliberate small imperfections or personal opinions to avoid sounding AI-generated","severity":"warning"},{"check":"Post targets one specific revenue stage, company size, or maturity level rather than broad category","severity":"warning"}]'::jsonb,
  '[{"type":"post_drafts","description":"An ICP-targeted LinkedIn post (3x per week minimum) with explicit audience call-out, industry jargon, specific valuable insight, and clear CTA"}]'::jsonb,
  ARRAY['linkedin', 'magnetlab_post_writer']::text[],
  ARRAY['0-1', '0-2']::text[],
  1
)
