VALUES (
  'm2',
  '2-5',
  'Validate Emails',
  $body$:::info Build Context
:::

## Steps

1. Export the email column from your Clay table as a CSV.
2. Upload to ZeroBounce. Run validation. This removes obviously invalid emails (non-existent domains, syntax errors, etc.).
3. From ZeroBounce results, identify all "catch-all" emails (addresses like hello@company.com that accept everything but may not deliver).
4. Upload the catch-all emails to BounceBan. Run secondary validation.
5. Merge the validated results back into your Clay table.
6. Mark invalid/risky emails for exclusion. Only send to validated addresses.$body$,
