INSERT INTO program_sops (module_id, sop_number, title, content, quality_bars, deliverables, tools_used, dependencies, version)
VALUES (
  'm3',
  '3-107',
  'LinkedIn Algorithm Changes and Platform Evolution (2025)',
  $body$## Overview
In 2025 LinkedIn shifted from a social graph (content shown to your connections) to a content graph (top-performing content shown to anyone, TikTok-style). Follower count no longer drives distribution; content quality and format do.

## Steps

1. **Internalize the Core Shift** — LinkedIn's AI now surfaces high-performing posts to relevant users regardless of connection status; your follower count is no longer your moat.

:::tip From the Field
LinkedIn now uses the actual words in your post to determine who sees it — write with hyper-specific ICP language (job titles, pain points, industry terms) because topical keyword relevance is the new distribution lever, not your follower list.
:::


2. **Stop Mass-Connecting for Reach** — Growing connections as a distribution strategy yields diminishing returns under the content graph; invest that time in content instead.

:::tip From the Field
Manual ICP-adjacent prospecting: find one ideal client, open their connections, and cherry-pick 25-30 good-fit prospects per day (~30% accept). Their second-degree network self-selects for ICP fit, and once connected, your lead magnet posts get algorithmically amplified to *their* connections — compounding organic reach without paid spend.
:::


3. **Prioritize Quality Over Frequency** — One post that generates early engagement outperforms five mediocre ones. Bar: "Would someone with zero context about me stop scrolling for this?"

4. **Use Lead Magnets While They Work** — Comment-to-get posts still drive strong engagement signals, but performance is declining. Treat them as a tactic with a shelf life.

5. **Benchmark Against Your Own Recent Posts** — Organic reach is down platform-wide in 2025, even for 50k+ follower accounts. Do not compare to 2023-era numbers.

6. **Treat LinkedIn as a Discovery Platform** — Small accounts can blow up overnight; new competitors can appear from nowhere. Factor this into GTM planning.

7. **Diversify Beyond Organic** — Pair organic content with LinkedIn DMs/voice notes, outbound email, and paid ads. Organic alone is no longer sufficient for pipeline.

## Key Lessons

- Someone with 1,000 followers gets roughly the same baseline impressions as someone with 50,000 on regular posts.
- The algorithm rewards content performance, not tenure or title -- 19-year-olds with AI lead magnets can outgrow established executives.
- Lead magnets are the current meta but already showing diminishing returns.
- Platform-wide reach decline is real; adjust KPIs accordingly.
- Early movers on new formats get outsized distribution before saturation.

## Common Mistakes

- Assuming low engagement means your content is broken when it is a platform-wide trend.
- Spending weeks growing connections as a distribution play under the old social-graph logic.
- Copying generic "comment GUIDE to get my free PDF" without differentiation.
- Dismissing small-follower competitors who can now build visibility rapidly.
- Relying solely on LinkedIn organic for pipeline when reach is declining.$body$,
  '[{"check":"Content uses hyper-specific ICP language (job titles, pain points, industry terms) rather than generic messaging","severity":"critical"},{"check":"Each post clears the bar: ''Would someone with zero context about me stop scrolling for this?''","severity":"critical"},{"check":"Lead magnet posts are differentiated and not generic ''comment GUIDE'' copies","severity":"warning"},{"check":"Performance benchmarked against own recent posts, not 2023-era historical data","severity":"warning"},{"check":"Organic LinkedIn paired with DMs, outbound email, and/or paid ads for pipeline diversification","severity":"info"}]'::jsonb,
  '[{"type":"content_plan","description":"Strategy for prioritizing quality content posts with hyper-specific ICP language over frequency, using lead magnets while they work, and benchmarking against recent performance"},{"type":"outreach_campaign","description":"Manual ICP-adjacent prospecting approach targeting 25-30 good-fit prospects daily from ideal client''s second-degree network"}]'::jsonb,
  ARRAY['linkedin', 'linkedin_ads_manager']::text[],
  ARRAY[]::text[],
  1
)
