INSERT INTO program_sops (module_id, sop_number, title, content, quality_bars, deliverables, tools_used, dependencies, version)
VALUES (
  'm5',
  '5-1',
  'Set Up LinkedIn Ads Account & Insight Tag',
  $body$:::info Build Context
:::

## Why This Matters

LinkedIn organic reach is declining every day — the same trajectory Facebook pages went through. A thousand lead-magnet comments may yield 800 people who are not your ICP. LinkedIn Ads gives you **precision targeting + guaranteed reach**, and you pay with money instead of time. The Insight Tag is LinkedIn's equivalent of the Facebook Pixel and lets you build a retargeting audience passively over time.

## Steps

1. Go to **business.linkedin.com** and sign in.
2. Go to **Account Settings → Billing**. Add your credit card and tax ID.
3. Go to **Measurements → Insights → Manage Sources → Insight Tag**.
4. Click **"I'll install the tag myself."** Hit Proceed.
5. Copy the tag code snippet.
6. **Install the tag on every page in your business** — landing pages, thank-you pages, booking pages, your main website. There is no downside. Even though the ads we run are engagement-based (not click-based), the tag passively grows your retargeting audience over time.

:::tip Magnet Lab Integration
If you use Magnet Lab to host your landing pages, go to **Settings** in Magnet Lab. There is a full **LinkedIn Ads Conversion API** implementation built in. It passes every piece of data back to the LinkedIn Ads Conversion API automatically — the best possible implementation of LinkedIn Ads page-building data.
:::

:::info Real-World Example
Magnet Lab's integration is server-side (Conversion API), not just the browser-based Insight Tag pixel. To set it up: generate an access token in LinkedIn Campaign Manager, authenticate it, then paste it into Magnet Lab's LinkedIn Insight Tag connection field — same concept as a server-side Meta pixel.
:::

## Key Principle

> "I'm a performance marketer and I hate the idea of wasting data. I have to save every bit of data I can get." — Tim Keen

Even if you run engagement-only campaigns where clicks don't matter much, you are gradually building a remarketing audience that becomes valuable later. Install the tag everywhere. There is zero negative.

:::warning Common Question
**"Do I need separate Insight Tags for separate campaigns?"** No. One tag captures all website visitors regardless of which campaign drove them. You distinguish audiences through custom audience lists you upload in Campaign Manager, not through separate tags.
:::

## Ad Account vs. Personal Account

Your **ad account** is a container for billing and campaign management. It is separate from your personal LinkedIn profile. You can name it anything — your business name, your personal name, it doesn't matter. An ad account can run posts from **any** individual LinkedIn profile or business page, as long as that person grants approval.

## Common Mistake

Do **NOT** click the "Boost Post" button that appears on your organic posts. That button creates an automated campaign with no control over audience, bidding, or the "casino" settings. It is a "give LinkedIn free money" button. You will set up campaigns manually in Campaign Manager instead.$body$,
  '[{"check":"Insight Tag installed on every business website page (landing pages, thank-you pages, booking pages, main website)","severity":"critical"},{"check":"LinkedIn ad account billing and tax ID properly configured before running campaigns","severity":"critical"},{"check":"Avoid using ''Boost Post'' button; instead, manually set up campaigns in Campaign Manager with full audience and bidding control","severity":"warning"},{"check":"If using Magnet Lab, Conversion API integration configured with valid access token for server-side tracking","severity":"warning"},{"check":"Single Insight Tag captures all website visitors; audiences segmented through custom audience lists in Campaign Manager, not separate tags","severity":"info"}]'::jsonb,
  '[{"type":"email_infrastructure","description":"LinkedIn Ads account configured with billing, Insight Tag installed on all business website pages, and retargeting audience building infrastructure in place"}]'::jsonb,
  ARRAY['linkedin_ads_manager', 'magnetlab_creator']::text[],
  ARRAY[]::text[],
  1
)
