INSERT INTO program_sops (module_id, sop_number, title, content, quality_bars, deliverables, tools_used, dependencies, version)
VALUES (
  'm5',
  '5-2',
  'Upload Your TAM as a Matched Audience',
  $body$:::info Build Context
:::

## Why This Matters

LinkedIn Ads is a casino. The only way to win is to become an expert card counter. If you use LinkedIn's built-in targeting options, you're playing into their hands. You need to create audiences that **force the platform to do what you want**. Uploading a matched audience of your exact TAM is how you take control.

## Two Audience Types

You should create **both** and test both:

| Type | Match Rate | Precision | When to Use |
|------|-----------|-----------|-------------|
| **Contact list** (individual people) | ~80% | 100% certainty these are ICP | When you want zero waste — every person shown the ad is someone you chose |
| **Company list** (company names) | ~90% | Need to layer job-title filters on top | When you want broader reach within target companies |

## Steps: Contact List Upload

1. Export your TAM from Clay (or your list tool) as a CSV.
2. Download LinkedIn's CSV template from the audience upload screen.
3. Open the template in Google Sheets. Copy and paste your data columns into the template.
4. **Match column headers exactly:** Email, First Name, Last Name, Job Title, Employee, Company, Country. Delete columns you don't have (e.g., Google Aid).

:::danger Critical: The @ Symbol Trap
Before uploading, select the **Job Title** column. Do a **Find & Replace**: search for `@` and replace with nothing. LinkedIn scans for `@` and assumes any column containing it is an email column. If someone's headline is "Founder @ Innovation Catalyst," your entire file will be rejected. This one fix will save you 20+ minutes of frustration.
:::

5. In LinkedIn Campaign Manager, go to **Plan → Audiences → Create Audience → Matched Audience**.
6. Choose source: **Contact list**.
7. Upload your cleaned CSV.
8. Wait **24–48 hours** for matching.

## Steps: Company List Upload

1. Same process — download LinkedIn's company template.
2. Required columns: Company Name, LinkedIn Company Page URL. That's usually all you need.
3. You can delete the Stock Symbol and Industry columns — LinkedIn is extremely good at matching companies by name alone.
4. Upload and wait 24–48 hours.

## After Upload: Narrowing Company Lists

If you uploaded a company list, you need to narrow the audience to your ICP within those companies:

1. In the campaign setup, click **Narrow Audience Further**.
2. Click **Audience Attributes → Job Experience → Job Titles**.
3. Enter the specific job titles you're targeting (e.g., "Chief Executive Officer," "Founder," "Co-Founder").
4. Optionally add **Company Size** as a secondary filter.
5. Avoid **Seniority** — it's often inaccurate on LinkedIn.

:::info Real-World Example
A 10,000-company list matched to ~2.4 million people on LinkedIn, of which only ~7,350 (less than 0.3%) were actual ICP — this is why job title filtering on company lists is non-negotiable. Run contact list and company list as separate ad sets and compare performance directly.
:::

## Audience Size Guidance

There is no minimum audience size to make this work. If your TAM is 2,000 people, that's fine. If it's 150 private-equity owners of dental service organizations, that's fine too — as long as your contract value justifies the higher CPM. The smaller the audience, the higher the CPM, but if you're speaking the language of your ICP and you sell high-ticket services, it doesn't matter.$body$,
  '[{"check":"CSV column headers match LinkedIn''s required format exactly (Email, First Name, Last Name, Job Title, Employee, Company, Country)","severity":"critical"},{"check":"@ symbol removed from Job Title column before upload to prevent file rejection","severity":"critical"},{"check":"Company list audiences include job title filtering to reduce ICP mismatch below 0.3% false positive rate","severity":"warning"},{"check":"Both contact list and company list audiences created and tested separately for performance comparison","severity":"warning"},{"check":"Audience matching completion verified within 24–48 hours before campaign launch","severity":"info"}]'::jsonb,
  '[{"type":"ad_targeting","description":"Matched audience of TAM contacts or companies uploaded to LinkedIn Ads for precise audience targeting"}]'::jsonb,
  ARRAY['clay', 'linkedin_ads_manager']::text[],
  ARRAY['5-1']::text[],
  1
)
