INSERT INTO program_sops (module_id, sop_number, title, content, quality_bars, deliverables, tools_used, dependencies, version)
VALUES (
  'm5',
  '5-3',
  'Create a Thought Leadership Ad Campaign',
  $body$## Why Thought Leadership Ads

Thought leadership ads look native, leverage the social proof you're already generating organically, and require no additional creative. They're also slightly annoying to set up — which is great, because it means fewer competitors will do it.

We only teach **one** LinkedIn Ads format. This is the 80/20 — the format that delivers the highest ROI for high-ticket B2B services.

## The 6 Gauntlets

LinkedIn Campaign Manager is designed to extract maximum spend from you. Every default setting benefits LinkedIn, not you. You must disable each "gauntlet" manually.

## Steps

1. In Campaign Manager, click **Create → Create Campaign**.
2. Name it descriptively (e.g., "TL — Lead Magnet — Claims Managers").
3. **Campaign Objective:** Select **ENGAGEMENT**. Not website visits, not conversions.
4. Run continuously or set a start/end date — doesn't matter for now.

### Gauntlet 1: Targeting Mode
5. Click **Classic** (not "Accelerate").
6. Click **Standard Ad Creation** (not the simplified version).

### Gauntlet 2: Audience
7. Add an ad set within the campaign.
8. Under audience, click **Close → Reset Audience**.
9. Choose **List Upload** as source.
10. Select your contact list or company list.
11. If using a **company list**, click **Narrow Audience Further → Audience Attributes → Job Experience → Job Titles** and filter to your ICP titles.

### Gauntlet 3: Audience Expansion
12. **Disable "Enable Audience Expansion."** This checkbox lets LinkedIn show your ads to people outside your list. Turn it OFF.

### Gauntlet 4: Audience Network
13. **Disable "LinkedIn Audience Network."** This would show your ads on third-party sites. Turn it OFF.

### Gauntlet 5: Location
14. Change location setting from "recent or permanent" to **"Permanent location"** only. "Recent location" lets LinkedIn target people who have recently traveled to a location — this inflates the audience with irrelevant people.

### Ad Format
15. Choose **Single Image** or **Video** — these are the only two formats that support thought leadership ads.

### Gauntlet 6: Budget & Bidding
16. Set a low daily budget to start: **$30/day**.
17. Click **"Show additional settings."**
18. Switch bidding strategy to **Manual Bidding**.
19. **Disable "Enable bid adjustment for high value clicks."**
20. LinkedIn will show a recommended bid range (e.g., "$3.82 – $11.74"). Set your bid at **20–50% below the lowest recommendation** (e.g., if lowest is $3.82, bid $3.00).

:::warning The "Boost Post" Trap
The "Boost" button on organic posts turns all six gauntlets back ON automatically. It uses maximum delivery bidding, audience expansion, audience network, and recent location. Never use it. Always set up campaigns manually through Campaign Manager.
:::

## Pre-Launch Checklist

Before clicking "Next" to create ads, verify:

- [ ] Objective = Engagement
- [ ] Classic targeting mode selected
- [ ] Matched audience (contact or company list) loaded
- [ ] If company list: job title narrowing applied
- [ ] Audience Expansion = OFF
- [ ] LinkedIn Audience Network = OFF
- [ ] Location = Permanent only
- [ ] Format = Single Image or Video
- [ ] Manual bidding enabled
- [ ] Bid = 20–50% below lowest recommendation
- [ ] Bid adjustment for high value clicks = OFF$body$,
  '[{"check":"All 6 gauntlets disabled per SOP requirements (Audience Expansion, Audience Network, bid adjustment, targeting mode, location set to permanent only)","severity":"critical"},{"check":"Campaign objective set to ENGAGEMENT only — not website visits or conversions","severity":"critical"},{"check":"Manual bidding enabled with bid set 20–50% below LinkedIn''s lowest recommendation","severity":"critical"},{"check":"Campaign created through Campaign Manager, never via the ''Boost Post'' button","severity":"warning"},{"check":"Audience matched via List Upload (contact or company list) with ICP job title filtering applied if using company list","severity":"warning"}]'::jsonb,
  '[{"type":"ad_campaign","description":"A LinkedIn thought leadership ad campaign configured with manual gauntlet disabling, manual bidding, and matched audience targeting"}]'::jsonb,
  ARRAY['linkedin_ads_manager']::text[],
  ARRAY[]::text[],
  1
)
