INSERT INTO program_sops (module_id, sop_number, title, content, quality_bars, deliverables, tools_used, dependencies, version)
VALUES (
  'm5',
  '5-4',
  'Select & Approve Posts as Thought Leadership Ads',
  $body$:::info Build Context
:::

## The Strategy: Organic First, Then Boost

Do **not** think about writing ads. Just write regular lead-magnet posts, post them, see which ones perform well organically, and boost those as ads. Thinking is overrated — the market tells you what it wants.

Every week (or as often as possible), create a new valuable lead magnet. The market gives you feedback on which ones resonate. Boost the winners. This removes all guesswork.

## Step 1: Edit the Post to Include a Link

Before boosting a lead-magnet post, **edit** the original LinkedIn post to add a direct opt-in link in the body text.

Why this works:
- You are paying for **engagement** (not clicks), so link clicks don't cost you anything extra.
- Your ICP is guaranteed to see these posts because you're targeting them with your matched audience.

:::tip From the Field
Adding a link to a boosted post has zero downside — the algorithm's link penalty only affects organic reach, which the ad bypasses entirely. The "comment to get" CTA also hacks LinkedIn's engagement-optimized ad delivery: the algorithm sees real engagement signals and rewards the ad with better distribution, so you're simultaneously generating leads AND improving ad performance. If using MagnetLab, link tracking will show exactly who clicked.
:::

- You're making their lives easier — they can comment OR click, whichever they prefer.

Example addition to the end of a post:
> "By the way, you can click here to get access right away: [link to opt-in page]"

:::tip Link to the opt-in page, not the resource itself
You want their email. Always link to the landing page, not directly to the PDF or resource.
:::

## Step 2: Request Access from Your Ad Account

Your ad account and personal profile are separate entities. You need to grant your ad account permission to run your personal posts.

1. In the ad creation screen within your campaign, click **"Browse Existing Content."**
2. Search for your own name.
3. LinkedIn will show your recent posts. For any post you want to run, click to request access.
4. LinkedIn sends an approval email. You can also click **"View Request → Copy Request Link"** and open it in a new tab while logged into your personal LinkedIn.

## Step 3: Enable Auto-Approval (Recommended)

To skip the approval process for every future post:

1. Open the request link in your personal LinkedIn browser session.
2. Look for the **"Auto Approval"** toggle — it will say "Auto approval off."
3. Toggle it **ON**.
4. All future posts from your personal profile are now automatically available as ads in your ad account. No more per-post approvals.

:::note Finding Posts
If search is finicky, you can also grab the direct URL of any LinkedIn post and paste it into the "Browse Existing Content" search field. This is the most reliable method.
:::

## Step 4: Choose What to Boost

Only two types of posts are worth boosting:

| Post Type | Purpose | CTA |
|-----------|---------|-----|
| **Lead magnet posts** | Top of funnel — generate opt-ins | "Comment [keyword] below" + opt-in link |
| **Case study / testimonial posts** | Bottom of funnel — drive bookings | "Book a call" link or calendar link |

Run these in **separate ad groups** within your campaign so you can track performance independently.

## Step 5: Understand the Comment + Ad Interaction

When someone comments on your boosted post, **LeadShark** picks up that engagement and can auto-deliver the lead magnet via DM — exactly the same as it would for an organic post. The difference is that ads guarantee your ICP sees the post.

This creates a dual path:
- **Path A (comment):** They comment → LeadShark DMs them → conversation begins
- **Path B (link):** They click the link → opt-in page → email sequence begins

Both paths feed into your funnel. Test both and see which converts better for your audience.

## Using Other People's Posts

You can also search for and request permission to run **anyone's** LinkedIn posts as ads through your ad account. If a team member, partner, or client has a great post, you can amplify it with your budget and targeting. They just need to approve the request.$body$,
  '[{"check":"All boosted lead-magnet posts include direct opt-in link in post body (not just in comments)","severity":"critical"},{"check":"Ad account access is requested and approved before launching ad campaign","severity":"critical"},{"check":"Lead magnet posts and case study/testimonial posts run in separate ad groups for performance tracking","severity":"warning"},{"check":"Link destination is opt-in landing page, not direct resource download","severity":"warning"},{"check":"Auto-approval is enabled to streamline future post boosting workflow","severity":"info"}]'::jsonb,
  '[{"type":"ad_campaign","description":"Approved boosted LinkedIn posts structured as thought leadership ads with separate ad groups for lead magnets and case studies"}]'::jsonb,
  ARRAY['linkedin_ads_manager', 'linkedin', 'leadshark', 'magnetlab_creator']::text[],
  ARRAY['5-3']::text[],
  1
)
