INSERT INTO program_sops (module_id, sop_number, title, content, quality_bars, deliverables, tools_used, dependencies, version)
VALUES (
  'm6',
  '6-103',
  'AI Tool Limitations and Honest Service Positioning',
  $body$:::info Auto-Generated
This SOP was created from patterns identified across multiple coaching and sales calls. It will continue to evolve as new knowledge is captured.
:::

## Overview
AI tools generate impressive outputs fast but fail at consistency, brand nuance, and security. When offering services outside your core expertise, how you position your experience level determines whether you build or break trust.

## Steps

### Part A: Evaluating AI Tools for Client Work

1. **Acknowledge the paradox** -- AI is "very smart and very dumb." It struggles with consistency, state management, and fine details, so every output needs human oversight.
2. **Test AI against your current workflow** -- Run a head-to-head comparison (speed, quality, brand consistency, revision effort) before committing to AI for any client deliverable.
3. **Use AI for ideation and first drafts; keep humans on brand-critical work** -- A Canva template built by an experienced designer beats AI-generated design for recurring branded deliverables.
4. **Never ship AI output without human review** -- Check fonts, layout, tone, factual accuracy, and brand guidelines before delivery.

### Part B: Security with AI Dev Tools

5. **Treat AI coding tools as a security risk** -- They can access and expose API keys, credentials, and tokens across your file system.
6. **Audit your environment first** -- Store keys in env vars or secret managers, configure `.gitignore`/`.env` properly, and know what data the tool can reach.
7. **Build security into the workflow** -- Mandate code review for exposed secrets, dependency scanning, and regular credentials rotation.

### Part C: Honest Positioning for New Services

8. **Be transparent about your experience level** -- Overpromising leads to broken trust and poor outcomes.
9. **Position your network as an asset** -- "I haven't run this exact campaign, but I'm part of a community of experts who do this daily with proven playbooks."
10. **Set appropriate expectations and over-deliver** -- Honesty lets clients calibrate, giving you room to learn and exceed expectations.

## Key Lessons
- AI won't understand client preferences or brand nuance that experienced professionals know intuitively.
- For recurring branded design (thumbnails, social templates), traditional tools with good templates beat AI generation.
- AI-assisted coding without security knowledge is one of the most dangerous trends in tech right now.
- Honesty about experience is a positioning strategy, not a weakness -- framing yourself as a connector to expertise is a legitimate value proposition.

## Common Mistakes
- Assuming AI output is client-ready without review.
- Replacing experienced judgment with AI to cut costs -- time saved on generation is lost on corrections and client dissatisfaction.
- Using AI coding tools without understanding what data they can access, leading to leaked credentials.
- Overstating expertise to win a deal, then failing to deliver.
- Being so self-deprecating you undermine confidence -- the right frame is "I'm learning this, I have great resources, and I'll deliver results."$body$,
  '[{"check":"All AI-generated outputs reviewed for brand consistency, tone, factual accuracy, and fonts before client delivery","severity":"critical"},{"check":"API keys, credentials, and tokens stored in env vars/secret managers and never exposed to AI tools","severity":"critical"},{"check":"Service positioning frames lack of direct experience as access to proven playbooks and expert network, not as incompetence","severity":"warning"},{"check":"AI used only for ideation and first drafts; brand-critical work retained by experienced humans","severity":"warning"},{"check":"Client expectations explicitly set to align with experience level, creating room to exceed delivery","severity":"info"}]'::jsonb,
  '[{"type":"operating_playbook","description":"Framework for evaluating AI tools, managing security risks, and positioning services honestly to clients"}]'::jsonb,
  ARRAY[]::text[],
  ARRAY[]::text[],
  1
)
