INSERT INTO program_sops (module_id, sop_number, title, content, quality_bars, deliverables, tools_used, dependencies, version)
VALUES (
  'm6',
  '6-107',
  'Transcript Management and Knowledge Systems',
  $body$## Overview
Every call contains extractable insights about objections, positioning, market signals, and process gaps. This SOP turns scattered transcripts into a living, queryable knowledge system that compounds with every conversation.

## Steps

1. **Record every call** -- Use Fireflies, Otter, Fathom, or your platform's native transcription. No call goes unrecorded unless someone opts out.
2. **Manually review the first 10-20 transcripts** -- Before automating anything, read them yourself to learn what insight types actually appear, what patterns matter, and whether your outreach/positioning is resonating.
3. **Tag and extract knowledge entries** -- Categorize into: objections and responses, positioning insights, market signals, process lessons, and client language (exact phrases prospects use to describe problems).
4. **Ingest into a RAG system** -- Feed extracted entries and full transcripts into a retrieval-augmented generation system so any team member or AI assistant can query it on demand.
5. **Process every call immediately** -- This is a post-call habit, not a quarterly cleanup. The more consistently you feed the system, the more valuable it becomes.
6. **Use it as a daily reference layer** -- Query before sales calls for relevant objections, before writing outreach for client language, before coaching for recurring patterns.
7. **Automate gradually** -- Only build auto-extraction workflows after you've done enough manual review to know what matters and why.

## Key Lessons
- Transcripts are compounding business intelligence, not just call records.

:::tip From the Field
If you run any business where you deliver value on calls, you should be keeping transcripts of every single call -- you're throwing away your most valuable asset if you don't. These transcripts become the raw material for all your content creation; you never really have to write anything from scratch if you're capturing the value you deliver verbally.
:::

- A RAG-based knowledge system turns scattered conversations into a queryable, living playbook that gets smarter with every call.
- Manual-first review builds the intuition to know what matters before you hand the process to automation.
- The discipline is in the consistency: process every call, every time, no exceptions.

## Common Mistakes
- Letting transcripts pile up unprocessed -- a backlog of unreviewed recordings is a backlog of lost knowledge.
- Jumping straight to automation before manually reviewing enough calls to know what signal vs. noise looks like.
- Reading a transcript once and filing it away instead of enriching a persistent system.
- Dumping raw transcripts without tagging by type (objection, positioning, market signal, process lesson).
- Keeping the knowledge system siloed to one person instead of making it a shared, queryable resource.$body$,
  '[{"check":"Every call is recorded and transcribed with no exceptions (opt-out only)","severity":"critical"},{"check":"First 10-20 transcripts are manually reviewed before any automation is built","severity":"critical"},{"check":"All extracted knowledge entries are tagged by type (objection, positioning, market signal, process lesson, client language)","severity":"critical"},{"check":"Knowledge system is queryable and accessible to all team members, not siloed to one person","severity":"warning"},{"check":"Calls are processed immediately after completion, not allowed to pile up in backlog","severity":"warning"},{"check":"Knowledge system is actively referenced before sales calls, outreach writing, and coaching sessions","severity":"info"}]'::jsonb,
  '[{"type":"operating_playbook","description":"A queryable, RAG-based knowledge system containing extracted insights from call transcripts (objections, responses, positioning language, market signals, process lessons, and client language) that serves as a living reference for sales, content, and coaching"}]'::jsonb,
  ARRAY['fireflies', 'fathom', 'grain']::text[],
  ARRAY[]::text[],
  1
)
