INSERT INTO program_sops (module_id, sop_number, title, content, quality_bars, deliverables, tools_used, dependencies, version)
VALUES (
  'm7',
  '7-101',
  'AI-Powered Content Automation and Repurposing',
  $body$## Overview
Stop writing content from scratch. Your sales calls, coaching sessions, and existing assets already contain everything you need. This SOP turns those conversations into a reliable stream of draft content using AI.

## Steps

1. **Record and transcribe every call** -- Use Fathom, Fireflies, Otter, or native platform transcription. Not recording is throwing away your best content material daily.
2. **Feed each transcript to a content-mining GPT** -- Extract 10 potential post ideas per call: pain points, objections handled, frameworks explained, stories told, counterintuitive insights, concrete results. Save to a running idea bank.
3. **Score and select the 2-3 strongest ideas** -- Prioritize where you had a strong opinion, the prospect reacted positively, or the topic maps to a buying trigger for your offer.
4. **Draft posts with a second AI tool** -- Convert each idea into a LinkedIn-ready draft using your voice guidelines and preferred structure (hook, story, lesson, CTA). Expect 5-10 minutes of editing per draft.
5. **Repurpose existing assets** -- Audit slide decks, proposals, case studies, email threads, SOPs, workshop recordings, and Loom walkthroughs. Each can be broken into multiple posts using the same workflow.

:::tip From the Field
Pre-AI version of this system: write between calls — use the gap on your calendar immediately after a call to draft a post about something you just said. If you're delivering value on calls, that content is already relevant. This is the fallback workflow when AI tooling isn't set up yet, and it's what the automated pipeline is designed to replace.
:::

6. **Batch, schedule, and iterate** -- Queue posts into a scheduling tool (Taplio, Shield, or native LinkedIn). Stay 1-2 weeks ahead. Review engagement data and feed patterns back into your content-mining prompt.

## Key Lessons
- Your calls ARE the content -- the insights and frameworks you share verbally every day just need to be captured and reformatted.
- AI solves the volume problem, not the thinking problem. The volume needed to compete on LinkedIn makes AI tooling a practical necessity.
- Quality comes from heavily iterated, deep prompts -- not off-the-shelf generic instructions.
- Default to "what existing material can I reshape?" instead of creating from scratch. This cuts production time by 70-80%.

## Common Mistakes
- Not recording calls at all -- without transcripts, the entire system breaks down.
- Staring at a blank page instead of starting from a transcript excerpt, client question, or existing asset.
- Using generic AI prompts and accepting first output -- iterate aggressively and always edit before publishing.
- Waiting until you feel ready instead of shipping imperfect posts from real conversations (they outperform polished posts written in a vacuum).
- Treating this as a one-time setup instead of a weekly loop that improves as you refine prompts and build your idea bank.$body$,
  '[{"check":"Every call is recorded and transcribed; no verbal content is lost","severity":"critical"},{"check":"AI prompts are iterated and deeply customized, not generic templates; first output is never published without editing","severity":"critical"},{"check":"Post drafts are sourced from actual call transcripts, client questions, or existing assets rather than written from scratch","severity":"warning"},{"check":"Content is batched and scheduled 1-2 weeks ahead; engagement data is reviewed and fed back into prompts weekly","severity":"warning"},{"check":"Imperfect posts from real conversations are shipped rather than waiting for perfection; authentic content outperforms polished vacuum-written posts","severity":"info"}]'::jsonb,
  '[{"type":"post_drafts","description":"LinkedIn-ready post drafts (2-3 per call minimum) extracted from call transcripts and existing assets, edited and batched for scheduling"},{"type":"content_plan","description":"Content calendar and idea bank (10 ideas per call) scored for relevance and batched 1-2 weeks ahead"}]'::jsonb,
  ARRAY['fathom', 'fireflies', 'magnetlab_brain']::text[],
  ARRAY[]::text[],
  1
)
